<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 27 at 12:30PM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Willacy
County through 115 PM CDT...
At 1229 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Porfirio, or 11 miles east of Lyford, moving southwest at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
San Perlita, Willamar, Santa Monica, Porfirio and San Perlita High
School.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
